    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.52"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">52</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        October 5
                        1972
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt and Mr. and Mrs. Young,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Please try to forgive this unforgiveable delay in writing to thank you for the very special evening you gave us last Thursday. We all learned a great deal about Mr. Neihardt and his writings, and nothing occured that would limit our affections for him.</p> 
                
                <p>Mrs. Young was helpful in every possible way, and Mr. Young contributed more than a little to our enjoyment.</p> 
                
                <p>We were interested in Dr. Neihardt's anecdotes, his comments on poetry, his thoughts on philosophy (what thought is not philosophy?) and in the very great grace with which he greeted and treated us.</p> 
                
                <p>Thanks also for the autographed books. These will be precious to us now, and precious to those we may hand them down to.</p> 
                
                <p>Again, thank you all. God bless you each.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Bill Reiger</signed>
                    <signed>Bill Regier
                    for Emily Uzendoski,
                    Rex Veeder, and 
                    himself.</signed> 
                
                    <add>
